# Data Retention and Purge

Ensure all local data has explicit retention boundaries and user-controlled purge paths.

## Requirements
- Define TTL and maximum size for logs, audit entries, and issue bundles.
- Default to the minimum necessary retention; avoid indefinite storage of PHI.
- Provide a user-visible "clear data" action that removes PHI, redaction maps, and cached artifacts.
- Purge transient caches on sign-out or when feature flags are disabled.

## PHI Handling
- Retain encrypted MPRs only as long as needed for local workflows.
- Avoid duplicating PHI across multiple stores; use a single source of truth.

## Verification
- Add tests to confirm TTL purge and size limits work under load.
